<h2>Delay (Echo)</h2>


<p>
Now we will add <em>delay</em> to our audio. This adds an <em>echo</em> to the sound. Think as if you were in a really big canyon. 
</p>
<ol>

<li>Record yourself saying ‚Äúthis clean or dry, this has delay‚Äù

<li>Trim the silence and normalize the track 
<ol>
 
<li><strong><em>Highlight</em></strong> the silence
 
<li>Press Backspace
 
<li>Go to <em>Effects -> Normalize</em>
</li> 
</ol>

<li>How, highlight the part of the audio where you say ‚Äúthis has delay‚Äù

<li>Click <em>Effects -> VST Effects -> mdaDelay.so</em>

<li>Click <em>Apply</em>

<li>Play the audio to make sure it‚Äôs correct. 
</li>
</ol>
