<h2>Reverb</h2>


<p>
Now we will add <em>reverb</em> to our audio. This makes it sound like your audio is happening in a room. People like this because it sounds more natural.
</p>
<ol>

<li>Record yourself saying ‚Äúthis clean, this is with reverb‚Äù

<li>Trim the silence and normalize the track 
<ol>
 
<li><strong><em>Highlight</em></strong> the silence
 
<li>Press Backspace
 
<li>Go to <em>Effects -> Normalize</em>
</li> 
</ol>

<li>How, highlight the part of the audio where you say ‚Äúthis is with reverb‚Äù

<li>Click <em>Effects -> VST Effects -> freeverb.so</em>

<li>Adjust the ‚Äúwet‚Äù and ‚Äúdry‚Äù sliders to get something like what I have 

<li>Click <em>Apply</em>

<li>Play the audio to make sure it‚Äôs correct. 
</li>
</ol>
